AR-023 through AR-033 implementation plan (1441 lines)\n├── task.md                     # Benchmark task description (Chinese)\n├── proposal.md / PROPOSAL.md   # Proposal documents\n├── requirements.txt            # Python dependencies\n├── configs/                    # LiteLLM Proxy configuration\n├── docs/                       # Token cost measurement design (Chinese)\n├── specs/                      # 43 AR specification files (SDD source docs)\n│   ├── cli-toolkit/            # AR-031, AR-032 specs\n│   ├── deployment/             # AR-026, AR-027, AR-028 specs\n│   ├── python-sdk/             # AR-033 specs\n│   ├── integrations/           # AR-023, AR-024 specs\n│   ├── ci-cd/                  # AR-030 specs\n│   ├── code-execution/\n│   ├── sandbox-orchestration/\n│   ├── session-routing/\n│   ├── session-store/\n│   ├── idle-cleanup/\n│   └── testing/                # TDD Manifest\n├── scripts/                    # Benchmark engine and tooling\n│   ├── engine.py               # Main benchmark driver (799 lines)\n│   ├── auditor.py              # LiteLLM token auditor\n│   ├── schema.py               # Data schema validation\n│   ├── report.py               # HTML report generation\n│   ├── compare.py              # Cross-run comparison\n│   ├── export.py               # CSV/JSON/Markdown export\n│   ├── preflight.py            # Environment validation\n│   └── adapters/               # CLI tool adapters\n│       ├── base.py             # StageRecord + BaseAdapter\n│       ├── claude_code.py\n│       ├── gemini_cli.py\n│       ├── cursor_cli.py\n│       └── opencode_cli.py\n├── workspaces/v5.1/            # Per-run isolated code workspaces\n│   └── opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/  # Current run\n└── results/runs/v5.1/          # _full.json + per-stage logs\n```\n\n**The 8-stage SDD workflow:**\n| Stage | Name | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| ST-0 | AR Input | Read AR description, build context |\n| ST-1 | Requirement Clarification | Model understands requirements |\n| ST-2 | Spec Incremental Design | Generate/modify OpenSpec files |\n| ST-3 | Design Incremental Design | Generate/modify design documents |\n| ST-4 | Task Decomposition | Break design into executable tasks |\n| ST-5 | Development Implementation | Actual code writing |\n| ST-6 | Consistency Verification | Verify implementation vs spec |\n| ST-6.5 | Original Code Equivalence | Ensure no regression |\n| ST-7 | Merge Archive | Merge changes to main branch |\n\n---\n\n### 2. What's in the cmd/cli Module\n\nThe `cmd/cli` module is the **AgentCube CLI toolkit** (`kubectl-agentcube`), a Python Typer-based CLI for AI agent lifecycle management. It lives in the workspace at:\n\n**Path:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/`\n\n**Package structure:**\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                     # Project metadata, entry point: kubectl-agentcube\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                    # __version__ = \"0.1.0\", exports app + runtimes\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── main.py                    # Typer app: pack, build, publish, invoke, status commands\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   └── pack_models.py             # MetadataOptions dataclass\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py            # PackRuntime: workspace validation, Dockerfile generation\n│   │   ├── build_runtime.py           # BuildRuntime: Docker image building\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py         # PublishRuntime: deploy to K8s\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          # InvokeRuntime: POST to agent endpoint\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py          # StatusRuntime: query agent status\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py        # AgentMetadata (Pydantic), MetadataService\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py          # DockerService: build, push, login, remove\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py            # KubernetesProvider: standard K8s Deployment+Service\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py      # AgentCubeProvider: AgentRuntime CRD management\n│   └── operations/\n│       └── __init__.py                # Placeholder\n├── examples/\n│   ├── hello-agent/                   # Example Python agent\n│   ├── math-agent/                    # Example Python agent\n│   └── java-agent/                    # Example Java agent\n└── tests/\n    ├── cli/                           # Command-level tests\n    ├── runtime/                       # Runtime class tests\n    ├── services/                      # Service/provider tests\n    ├── models/                        # Model validation tests\n    └── integration/                   # End-to-end tests\n```\n\n**Key CLI commands:** `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`\n**Provider flag:** `--provider` accepts `\"agentcube\"` (AgentRuntime CR) or `\"k8s\"` (Deployment+Service)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Provider Implementations (Reference Material)\n\nThere are **two provider implementations** you can reference:\n\n#### 3a. KubernetesProvider (Standard K8s)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` (238 lines)\n\n**Key characteristics:**\n- Uses `kubernetes` Python client (`AppsV1Api`, `CoreV1Api`)\n- Creates standard `Deployment` + `NodePort Service`\n- Methods: `deploy_agent()`, `wait_for_deployment_ready()`, `get_agent_status()`, `delete_agent()`\n- Graceful 404 handling on deletes\n- Name sanitization: `agent_name.lower().replace(\"_\", \"-\").replace(\".\", \"-\")`\n- Returns dict with `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `service_url`, `node_port`\n- Has graceful `ImportError` fallback for when kubernetes package is not installed\n\n#### 3b. AgentCubeProvider (CRD-based)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` (135 lines)\n\n**Key characteristics:**\n- Uses `kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi`\n- Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resources in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- Class constants: `CRD_GROUP`, `CRD_VERSION`, `CRD_PLURAL`\n- Methods: `deploy_agent_runtime()`, `get_agent_runtime()`, `_sanitize_name()`\n- Embeds `sessionTimeout: \"15m\"`, `maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`, `imagePullSecrets`\n- Falls back to `os.environ` for `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL`\n- Name sanitization with regex: `re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9\\-]\", \"-\", name.lower())`, truncates to 63 chars\n\n---\n\n### 4. AR-026 / K8s/AgentCube Provider Related Files\n\n**AR-026** is titled \"K8s/AgentCube Provider\" and covers the CLI toolkit, client-go library, and Python SDK.\n\n#### Spec and Design Documents:\n\n| File | Path | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| **PLAN.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md` | Lines 488-639 cover AR-026 (Helm Workload Manager templates) in detail |\n| **Deployment Spec** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/spec.md` | Helm chart, CRDs, Dockerfiles, Makefile targets |\n| **Deployment Design** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md` | Full Helm template analysis, RBAC rules, CRD definitions (271 lines) |\n| **CLI Toolkit Spec** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/spec.md` | CLI command specs including provider requirements (197 lines) |\n| **CLI Toolkit Design** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/design.md` | Full CLI design with all classes, models, dependencies (400 lines) |\n| **Generated Design** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/.../design.md` | 1331-line AR-026 design document generated during ST-3 |\n| **TDD Manifest** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` | Test contracts for all core modules |\n\n#### AR-026 ST-3 Log (Design Stage):\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-026_ST-3.log`\n\nThe ST-3 stage completed successfully (EXIT_CODE: 0). The agent:\n1. Read the `.sdd_prompt.md` which specified: \"Write design.md for AR-026 -- K8s/AgentCube Provider, Module: cmd/cli, Language: Python, Size: M\"\n2. Read existing spec files (cli-toolkit/design.md, python-sdk specs)\n3. Examined the project structure\n4. Wrote a comprehensive 1331-line `design.md` covering:\n   - Architecture (system diagram, component relationships, package layouts)\n   - Data Structures (AgentMetadata, MetadataOptions, all Runtime/Service classes)\n   - API Contracts (all 5 CLI commands, metadata format, Dockerfile templates)\n   - Error Handling patterns\n   - Testing Strategy (80+ test cases)\n   - Deployment Considerations\n   - Implementation Steps (9-phase, 20-day plan)\n   - Known Issues and Limitations\n   - Future Changes\n\n#### AR-026 Change Directory:\n\n**Path:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-026/`\n\nContains 4 files created during the SDD workflow:\n- `proposal.md` -- Created in ST-0 (scaffold with TODOs)\n- `design.md` -- Created in ST-0 (scaffold), then overwritten in ST-3 with full content\n- `delta-spec.md` -- Created in ST-0 (scaffold), then overwritten in ST-2 with full GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios\n- `tasks.md` -- Created in ST-0 (scaffold with TODOs)\n\n#### All AR-026 Stage Logs:\n\n| Stage | Log File | Status |\n|-------|----------|--------|\n| ST-0 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/.../AR-026_ST-0.log` | EXIT_CODE: 0 - Scaffolded changes/AR-026/ |\n| ST-1 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/.../AR-026_ST-1.log` | EXIT_CODE: 0 - Wrote proposal.md |\n| ST-2 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/.../AR-026_ST-2.log` | EXIT_CODE: 0 - Wrote delta-spec.md with 20+ scenarios |\n| ST-3 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/.../AR-026_ST-3.log` | EXIT_CODE: 0 - Wrote 1331-line design.md |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Staging Documents (ST-3 and Similar)\n\nAll ST-3 (and other stage) logs for the current run are at:\n\n**Directory:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/`\n\nThis directory contains **104 log files** covering AR-001 through AR-026, each with stages ST-0 through ST-3 (and beyond for earlier ARs). The naming pattern is: `AR-{NNN}_ST-{N}.log`\n\nKey AR-026 logs found:\n- `AR-026_ST-0.log` -- AR input / scaffolding\n- `AR-026_ST-1.log` -- Requirement clarification / proposal\n- `AR-026_ST-2.log` -- Spec incremental design / delta-spec\n- `AR-026_ST-3.log` -- Design incremental design / design.md\n\n---\n\n### 6. Test Patterns and How Providers Are Tested\n\n#### Test File Locations:\n\n| Test File | Path |\n|-----------|------|\n| K8s Provider Tests | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/.../cmd/cli/tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py` (203 lines) |\n| AgentCube Provider Tests | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/.../cmd/cli/tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py` (142 lines) |\n| Metadata Service Tests | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/.../cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py` |\n| Docker Service Tests | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/.../cmd/cli/tests/services/test_docker_service.py` |\n| CLI Command Tests | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/.../cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_status_command.py`, `test_invoke_command.py`, `test_build_command.py` |\n| Runtime Tests | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/.../cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_pack_runtime_*.py`, `test_build_runtime_*.py`, `test_publish_runtime.py`, `test_invoke_runtime.py`, `test_status_runtime.py` |\n| Integration Tests | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/.../cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_build_e2e.py` |\n\n#### Test Patterns Used:\n\n**1. Class-based test organization with descriptive class names:**\n```python\nclass TestK8sProvider_DeployAgent:\n    def test_creates_deployment_and_service(self) -> None: ...\n\nclass TestK8sProvider_WaitForReady:\n    def test_returns_when_deployment_ready(self) -> None: ...\n\nclass TestK8sProvider_WaitTimeout:\n    def test_raises_timeout_error_when_not_ready(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n**2. Mocking pattern -- patch the kubernetes client APIs:**\n```python\nmock_apps_api = MagicMock()\nmock_core_api = MagicMock()\nwith patch(\"agentcube.services.k8s_provider.client.AppsV1Api\", return_value=mock_apps_api):\n    with patch(\"agentcube.services.k8s_provider.client.CoreV1Api\", return_value=mock_core_api):\n        provider = KubernetesProvider(namespace=\"default\")\n        result = provider.deploy_agent(...)\n```\n\n**3. Asserting on API call arguments:**\n```python\nmock_apps_api.create_namespaced_deployment.assert_called_once()\ncall_kwargs = mock_api.create_namespaced_custom_object.call_args[1]\nbody = call_kwargs[\"body\"]\nassert body[\"spec\"][\"image\"] == \"registry.example.com/test-agent:v1.0.0\"\n```\n\n**4. Testing error handling with ApiException:**\n```python\nfrom kubernetes.client.rest import ApiException\nmock_apps_api.delete_namespaced_deployment.side_effect = ApiException(status=404)\n# Should not raise -- 404 is ignored\nprovider.delete_agent(\"nonexistent\")\n```\n\n**5. Environment variable fallback testing:**\n```python\nwith patch(\"agentcube.services.agentcube_provider.os.environ.get\", side_effect=lambda k: \"env-value\" if k == \"ROUTER_URL\" else None):\n    provider.deploy_agent_runtime(...)\n```\n\n**6. TDD Manifest requirements** (`/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md`):\n- Test/Code ratio must be > 0.4\n- Every source file must have a corresponding test file\n- Specific test contracts defined: Test-WM-1 through Test-CLI-1\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28661c385ffeJz7MauRKXybXBl","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775861906550,"end":1775862074363}}}}
