{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862270660,"sessionID":"ses_28661e1e4ffevPoFHX5USfhuNI","part":{"id":"prt_d79a2289e0014YqsM4CatNNLEe","messageID":"msg_d79a1a7770011Cb3mCK5OPR1u3","sessionID":"ses_28661e1e4ffevPoFHX5USfhuNI","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_273c6b8780a84803bc176181","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd/cli\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-026/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-026/design.md`, `changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** None\n\n## T1. KubernetesProvider — Fill Test Gaps\n\nStrengthen `KubernetesProvider` test coverage for auto-assigned NodePort, entrypoint parsing, and env var propagation.\n\n- [ ] 1.1 Test auto-assigned NodePort (no node_port arg) — verify `deploy_agent` returns the auto-assigned port from the created Service\n- [ ] 1.2 Test entrypoint parsing — verify `\"python main.py arg1\"` splits into `command=[\"python\"]`, `args=[\"main.py\", \"arg1\"]`\n- [ ] 1.3 Test empty entrypoint — verify `entrypoint=\"\"` produces `command=None`, `args=None`\n- [ ] 1.4 Test env_vars propagation — verify `V1EnvVar` objects are created with correct key/value pairs\n- [ ] 1.5 Test deployment labels — verify `labels={\"app\": sanitized_name}` are set on the pod template\n- [ ] 1.6 Test namespace in return dict — verify `namespace` key is present in the result dict\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py -v` — all new tests pass\n\n---\n\n## T2. KubernetesProvider — Add `update_agent` (Patch)\n\nAdd ability to patch an existing Deployment + Service (spec requires create-or-patch semantics).\n\n- [ ] 2.1 Implement `update_agent()` method — uses `patch_namespaced_deployment` and `patch_namespaced_service`\n- [ ] 2.2 Test successful patch — verify both Deployment and Service are updated\n- [ ] 2.3 Test patch with 404 fallback — if Deployment doesn't exist, fall back to `deploy_agent` (create)\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py -v -k update` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T3. KubernetesProvider — Add `delete_agent` Return Value\n\nMake `delete_agent` return a structured dict (spec requires `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}`).\n\n- [ ] 3.1 Change `delete_agent` return type from `None` to `Dict[str, Any]`\n- [ ] 3.2 Return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ...}` on success\n- [ ] 3.3 Update existing tests to assert on the return value\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py -v -k delete` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T4. AgentCubeProvider — Add `delete_agent_runtime`\n\nImplement deletion of AgentRuntime Custom Resources (currently missing).\n\n- [ ] 4.1 Implement `delete_agent_runtime(name)` — uses `delete_namespaced_custom_object`\n- [ ] 4.2 Test successful deletion — returns `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"name\", \"namespace\"}`\n- [ ] 4.3 Test 404 handling — ignores `ApiException(status=404)` gracefully\n- [ ] 4.4 Test non-404 errors — re-raises `ApiException` for other status codes\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py -v -k delete` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T5. AgentCubeProvider — Add `update_agent_runtime` (Patch)\n\nAdd ability to patch an existing AgentRuntime CR (spec requires create-or-patch semantics).\n\n- [ ] 5.1 Implement `update_agent_runtime()` — uses `patch_namespaced_custom_object`\n- [ ] 5.2 Test successful patch — verify CR is updated with new spec values\n- [ ] 5.3 Test patch with 404 fallback — if CR doesn't exist, fall back to `deploy_agent_runtime` (create)\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py -v -k update` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T6. AgentCubeProvider — Fill Test Gaps\n\nStrengthen `AgentCubeProvider` test coverage for edge cases.\n\n- [ ] 6.1 Test name sanitization: leading/trailing dashes — `\"--my-agent--\"` → `\"my-agent\"`\n- [ ] 6.2 Test name sanitization: empty after sanitization — `\"___\"` → `\"\"` (or minimal valid name)\n- [ ] 6.3 Test `get_agent_runtime` with non-404 ApiException — verifies re-raise behavior\n- [ ] 6.4 Test CR spec contains all required fields: `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata.name`, `metadata.namespace`, `spec.image`, `spec.port`, `spec.entrypoint`, `spec.env`, `spec.workloadManagerUrl`, `spec.routerUrl`, `spec.readinessProbe`, `spec.sessionTimeout`, `spec.maxSessionDuration`, `spec.imagePullSecrets`\n- [ ] 6.5 Test endpoint format — verify `endpoint` uses `{router_url}/v1/agents/{sanitized_name}`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py -v` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T7. PublishRuntime — Pass `env_vars` to Providers\n\nCurrently `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s` and `_publish_k8s` pass `env_vars={}`. Wire through metadata-based env vars.\n\n- [ ] 7.1 Extract env vars from `metadata` (or `options`) and pass to `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\n- [ ] 7.2 Extract env vars from `metadata` (or `options`) and pass to `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n- [ ] 7.3 Test env vars are forwarded for AgentCube provider\n- [ ] 7.4 Test env vars are forwarded for K8s provider\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v -k env` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T8. PublishRuntime — Test `_prepare_local_image` Docker Unavailable\n\nVerify `RuntimeError` is raised when Docker is unavailable in local build mode.\n\n- [ ] 8.1 Test `_prepare_local_image` raises `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` when `check_docker_available()` returns `False`\n- [ ] 8.2 Test `_prepare_local_image` raises `ValueError` when `image_url` is missing and metadata has no image URL\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v -k local_image` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T9. PublishRuntime — Test `_prepare_cloud_image` Resolution\n\nVerify cloud image URL resolution logic.\n\n- [ ] 9.1 Test returns `options[\"image_url\"]` when provided\n- [ ] 9.2 Test falls back to `metadata.image[\"url\"]` when options lack `image_url`\n- [ ] 9.3 Test raises `ValueError` when neither options nor metadata provide image URL\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v -k cloud_image` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T10. PublishRuntime — Test `_update_publish_metadata`\n\nVerify metadata is correctly updated after publishing.\n\n- [ ] 10.1 Test `agent_id` and `agent_endpoint` are written for AgentCube provider\n- [ ] 10.2 Test `agent_endpoint` falls back to `service_url` for K8s provider\n- [ ] 10.3 Test `k8s_deployment` dict is written with correct structure for both providers\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v -k update_publish` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T11. StatusRuntime — Handle Missing `k8s_deployment`\n\nWhen `metadata.k8s_deployment` is `None`, StatusRuntime should handle gracefully.\n\n- [ ] 11.1 Test `_get_cr_k8s_status` when `metadata.k8s_deployment` is `None` — uses `metadata.agent_name` as fallback\n- [ ] 11.2 Test `_get_k8s_status` when `metadata.k8s_deployment` is `None` — uses `metadata.agent_name` as fallback\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py -v -k missing` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T12. InvokeRuntime — Test Direct HTTP Invocation Path\n\nCover the `provider=\"k8s\"` code path in `InvokeRuntime`.\n\n- [ ] 12.1 Test `_direct_http_invocation` sends POST to endpoint with correct payload\n- [ ] 12.2 Test `_direct_http_invocation` adds `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header when `session_id` exists\n- [ ] 12.3 Test `_direct_http_invocation` raises on HTTP error (`response.raise_for_status()`)\n- [ ] 12.4 Test `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` with endpoint lacking `/v1/` — verify URL rewriting handles this edge case\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py -v -k direct` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T13. CLI — Add `pack` Command Tests\n\nThe `pack` CLI command has no dedicated test file.\n\n- [ ] 13.1 Test successful pack — exit code 0, success message with agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path\n- [ ] 13.2 Test pack with all options — `--agent-name`, `--language`, `--entrypoint`, `--port`, `--build-mode`, `--description`, `--output`\n- [ ] 13.3 Test pack failure without verbose — exit code 1, error message, no traceback\n- [ ] 13.4 Test pack failure with verbose — exit code 1, error message, traceback present\n- [ ] 13.5 Test pack help output — shows all options\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_pack_command.py -v` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T14. CLI — Add `publish` Command Tests\n\nThe `publish` CLI command has no dedicated test file.\n\n- [ ] 14.1 Test successful publish with `--provider agentcube` — exit code 0, shows Agent ID and Endpoint\n- [ ] 14.2 Test successful publish with `--provider k8s` — exit code 0, shows Deployment, Service, URL\n- [ ] 14.3 Test unsupported provider — exit code 1, error message\n- [ ] 14.4 Test invalid node port (below 30000) — exit code 1, error message\n- [ ] 14.5 Test invalid node port (above 32767) — exit code 1, error message\n- [ ] 14.6 Test publish with `--namespace`, `--replicas`, `--node-port` options\n- [ ] 14.7 Test publish help output — shows all options\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_publish_command.py -v` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T15. CLI — Add `invoke` Command Provider Routing Tests\n\nVerify the `--provider` flag correctly routes in the CLI invoke command.\n\n- [ ] 15.1 Test `--provider agentcube` invokes `InvokeRuntime` with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n- [ ] 15.2 Test `--provider k8s` invokes `InvokeRuntime` with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n- [ ] 15.3 Test default provider is `agentcube` when `--provider` is omitted\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_invoke_command.py -v -k provider` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T16. CLI — Add `status` Command Provider Routing Tests\n\nVerify the `--provider` flag correctly routes in the CLI status command.\n\n- [ ] 16.1 Test `--provider agentcube` queries AgentRuntime CR status\n- [ ] 16.2 Test `--provider k8s` queries Deployment status\n- [ ] 16.3 Test default provider is `agentcube` when `--provider` is omitted\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_status_command.py -v -k provider` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T17. Integration — Publish E2E (Mocked)\n\nEnd-to-end test for the publish flow with mocked K8s/Docker.\n\n- [ ] 17.1 Test full publish flow: pack → build (mocked) → publish (mocked K8s) → verify metadata updated\n- [ ] 17.2 Test publish with `--provider k8s` end-to-end: verifies Deployment + Service creation, wait for ready, metadata update\n- [ ] 17.3 Test publish with `--provider agentcube` end-to-end: verifies AgentRuntime CR creation, metadata update\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_publish_e2e.py -v` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T18. Integration — Invoke E2E (Mocked)\n\nEnd-to-end test for the invoke flow with mocked HTTP.\n\n- [ ] 18.1 Test full invoke flow: publish (mocked) → invoke (mocked HTTP) → verify response\n- [ ] 18.2 Test invoke with custom headers end-to-end\n- [ ] 18.3 Test invoke with session ID end-to-end — verifies `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_invoke_e2e.py -v` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T19. Integration — Status E2E (Mocked)\n\nEnd-to-end test for the status flow with mocked K8s.\n\n- [ ] 19.1 Test full status flow: publish (mocked) → status (mocked K8s) → verify Rich table output\n- [ ] 19.2 Test status for unpublished agent — exit code 1, guidance message\n- [ ] 19.3 Test status for deleted agent — shows `not_found` or `not_found_in_k8s`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_status_e2e.py -v` — all pass\n\n---\n\n## T20. Test/Code Ratio Verification\n\nEnsure test-to-code ratio meets TDD manifest requirement (> 0.4).\n\n- [ ] 20.1 Count source lines in `cmd/cli/agentcube/` (exclude `__pycache__`, `__init__.py`)\n- [ ] 20.2 Count test lines in `cmd/cli/tests/` (exclude `__pycache__`, `__init__.py`)\n- [ ] 20.3 Verify ratio > 0.4; if not, add missing tests\n- [ ] 20.4 Verify every source file has a corresponding test file (per TDD manifest)\n\n**Verification:** Run `find cmd/cli/agentcube -name '*.py' ! -name '__init__.py' | xargs wc -l` and `find cmd/cli/tests -name '*.py' ! -name '__init__.py' | xargs wc -l`, compute ratio\n\n---\n\n## T21. Full Test Suite Green\n\nRun the complete test suite to ensure no regressions.\n\n- [ ] 21.1 `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v` — all tests pass\n- [ ] 21.2 `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` — coverage report generated\n- [ ] 21.3 No import errors or type errors in test files\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v --tb=short` — 0 failures, 0 errors\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nT1 ──→ T2 ──→ T3\nT4 ──→ T5\nT6 (parallel with T1-T5)\nT7 ──→ T10\nT8 (parallel)\nT9 (parallel)\nT11 (parallel)\nT12 (parallel)\nT13 ──┐\nT14 ──┼──→ T17 ──→ T21\nT15 ──┤\nT16 ──┘\nT18 ──→ T21\nT19 ──→ T21\nT20 ──→ T21\n```\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| G1 — Provider Core | T1, T4, T6 | None |\n| G2 — Provider Extensions | T2, T3, T5 | T1, T4 |\n| G3 — Runtime Logic | T7, T8, T9, T10, T11, T12 | None |\n| G4 — CLI Commands | T13, T14, T15, T16 | None |\n| G5 — Integration | T17, T18, T19 | T14, T15, T16 |\n| G6 — Verification | T20, T21 | All above |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | All provider tests pass (K8s + AgentCube) | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/ -v` |\n| AC2 | All runtime tests pass (publish, status, invoke) | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/ -v` |\n| AC3 | All CLI command tests pass (pack, build, publish, invoke, status) | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/ -v` |\n| AC4 | All integration tests pass | `pytest cmd/cli/t