{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862281654,"sessionID":"ses_28661e1e4ffevPoFHX5USfhuNI","part":{"id":"prt_d79a3f1f3001rgvMBEGaF2MT36","messageID":"msg_d79a3cb46001T0skOANHoCpzs1","sessionID":"ses_28661e1e4ffevPoFHX5USfhuNI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_13079d05cd2e429ebb01768b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: > **Language:** Python\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-026/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-026/design.md`, `changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md`\n8: > **Dependency:** None\n9: \n10: ## T1. KubernetesProvider — Fill Test Gaps\n11: \n12: Strengthen `KubernetesProvider` test coverage for auto-assigned NodePort, entrypoint parsing, and env var propagation.\n13: \n14: - [ ] 1.1 Test auto-assigned NodePort (no node_port arg) — verify `deploy_agent` returns the auto-assigned port from the created Service\n15: - [ ] 1.2 Test entrypoint parsing — verify `\"python main.py arg1\"` splits into `command=[\"python\"]`, `args=[\"main.py\", \"arg1\"]`\n16: - [ ] 1.3 Test empty entrypoint — verify `entrypoint=\"\"` produces `command=None`, `args=None`\n17: - [ ] 1.4 Test env_vars propagation — verify `V1EnvVar` objects are created with correct key/value pairs\n18: - [ ] 1.5 Test deployment labels — verify `labels={\"app\": sanitized_name}` are set on the pod template\n19: - [ ] 1.6 Test namespace in return dict — verify `namespace` key is present in the result dict\n20: \n21: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py -v` — all new tests pass\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## T2. KubernetesProvider — Add `update_agent` (Patch)\n26: \n27: Add ability to patch an existing Deployment + Service (spec requires create-or-patch semantics).\n28: \n29: - [ ] 2.1 Implement `update_agent()` method — uses `patch_namespaced_deployment` and `patch_namespaced_service`\n30: - [ ] 2.2 Test successful patch — verify both Deployment and Service are updated\n31: - [ ] 2.3 Test patch with 404 fallback — if Deployment doesn't exist, fall back to `deploy_agent` (create)\n32: \n33: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py -v -k update` — all pass\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## T3. KubernetesProvider — Add `delete_agent` Return Value\n38: \n39: Make `delete_agent` return a structured dict (spec requires `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}`).\n40: \n41: - [ ] 3.1 Change `delete_agent` return type from `None` to `Dict[str, Any]`\n42: - [ ] 3.2 Return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ...}` on success\n43: - [ ] 3.3 Update existing tests to assert on the return value\n44: \n45: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py -v -k delete` — all pass\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## T4. AgentCubeProvider — Add `delete_agent_runtime`\n50: \n51: Implement deletion of AgentRuntime Custom Resources (currently missing).\n52: \n53: - [ ] 4.1 Implement `delete_agent_runtime(name)` — uses `delete_namespaced_custom_object`\n54: - [ ] 4.2 Test successful deletion — returns `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"name\", \"namespace\"}`\n55: - [ ] 4.3 Test 404 handling — ignores `ApiException(status=404)` gracefully\n56: - [ ] 4.4 Test non-404 errors — re-raises `ApiException` for other status codes\n57: \n58: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py -v -k delete` — all pass\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## T5. AgentCubeProvider — Add `update_agent_runtime` (Patch)\n63: \n64: Add ability to patch an existing AgentRuntime CR (spec requires create-or-patch semantics).\n65: \n66: - [ ] 5.1 Implement `update_agent_runtime()` — uses `patch_namespaced_custom_object`\n67: - [ ] 5.2 Test successful patch — verify CR is updated with new spec values\n68: - [ ] 5.3 Test patch with 404 fallback — if CR doesn't exist, fall back to `deploy_agent_runtime` (create)\n69: \n70: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py -v -k update` — all pass\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## T6. AgentCubeProvider — Fill Test Gaps\n75: \n76: Strengthen `AgentCubeProvider` test coverage for edge cases.\n77: \n78: - [ ] 6.1 Test name sanitization: leading/trailing dashes — `\"--my-agent--\"` → `\"my-agent\"`\n79: - [ ] 6.2 Test name sanitization: empty after sanitization — `\"___\"` → `\"\"` (or minimal valid name)\n80: - [ ] 6.3 Test `get_agent_runtime` with non-404 ApiException — verifies re-raise behavior\n81: - [ ] 6.4 Test CR spec contains all required fields: `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata.name`, `metadata.namespace`, `spec.image`, `spec.port`, `spec.entrypoint`, `spec.env`, `spec.workloadManagerUrl`, `spec.routerUrl`, `spec.readinessProbe`, `spec.sessionTimeout`, `spec.maxSessionDuration`, `spec.imagePullSecrets`\n82: - [ ] 6.5 Test endpoint format — verify `endpoint` uses `{router_url}/v1/agents/{sanitized_name}`\n83: \n84: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py -v` — all pass\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## T7. PublishRuntime — Pass `env_vars` to Providers\n89: \n90: Currently `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s` and `_publish_k8s` pass `env_vars={}`. Wire through metadata-based env vars.\n91: \n92: - [ ] 7.1 Extract env vars from `metadata` (or `options`) and pass to `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\n93: - [ ] 7.2 Extract env vars from `metadata` (or `options`) and pass to `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n94: - [ ] 7.3 Test env vars are forwarded for AgentCube provider\n95: - [ ] 7.4 Test env vars are forwarded for K8s provider\n96: \n97: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v -k env` — all pass\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## T8. PublishRuntime — Test `_prepare_local_image` Docker Unavailable\n102: \n103: Verify `RuntimeError` is raised when Docker is unavailable in local build mode.\n104: \n105: - [ ] 8.1 Test `_prepare_local_image` raises `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` when `check_docker_available()` returns `False`\n106: - [ ] 8.2 Test `_prepare_local_image` raises `ValueError` when `image_url` is missing and metadata has no image URL\n107: \n108: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v -k local_image` — all pass\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## T9. PublishRuntime — Test `_prepare_cloud_image` Resolution\n113: \n114: Verify cloud image URL resolution logic.\n115: \n116: - [ ] 9.1 Test returns `options[\"image_url\"]` when provided\n117: - [ ] 9.2 Test falls back to `metadata.image[\"url\"]` when options lack `image_url`\n118: - [ ] 9.3 Test raises `ValueError` when neither options nor metadata provide image URL\n119: \n120: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v -k cloud_image` — all pass\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## T10. PublishRuntime — Test `_update_publish_metadata`\n125: \n126: Verify metadata is correctly updated after publishing.\n127: \n128: - [ ] 10.1 Test `agent_id` and `agent_endpoint` are written for AgentCube provider\n129: - [ ] 10.2 Test `agent_endpoint` falls back to `service_url` for K8s provider\n130: - [ ] 10.3 Test `k8s_deployment` dict is written with correct structure for both providers\n131: \n132: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v -k update_publish` — all pass\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## T11. StatusRuntime — Handle Missing `k8s_deployment`\n137: \n138: When `metadata.k8s_deployment` is `None`, StatusRuntime should handle gracefully.\n139: \n140: - [ ] 11.1 Test `_get_cr_k8s_status` when `metadata.k8s_deployment` is `None` — uses `metadata.agent_name` as fallback\n141: - [ ] 11.2 Test `_get_k8s_status` when `metadata.k8s_deployment` is `None` — uses `metadata.agent_name` as fallback\n142: \n143: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py -v -k missing` — all pass\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## T12. InvokeRuntime — Test Direct HTTP Invocation Path\n148: \n149: Cover the `provider=\"k8s\"` code path in `InvokeRuntime`.\n150: \n151: - [ ] 12.1 Test `_direct_http_invocation` sends POST to endpoint with correct payload\n152: - [ ] 12.2 Test `_direct_http_invocation` adds `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header when `session_id` exists\n153: - [ ] 12.3 Test `_direct_http_invocation` raises on HTTP error (`response.raise_for_status()`)\n154: - [ ] 12.4 Test `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` with endpoint lacking `/v1/` — verify URL rewriting handles this edge case\n155: \n156: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py -v -k direct` — all pass\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ## T13. CLI — Add `pack` Command Tests\n161: \n162: The `pack` CLI command has no dedicated test file.\n163: \n164: - [ ] 13.1 Test successful pack — exit code 0, success message with agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path\n165: - [ ] 13.2 Test pack with all options — `--agent-name`, `--language`, `--entrypoint`, `--port`, `--build-mode`, `--description`, `--output`\n166: - [ ] 13.3 Test pack failure without verbose — exit code 1, error message, no traceback\n167: - [ ] 13.4 Test pack failure with verbose — exit code 1, error message, traceback present\n168: - [ ] 13.5 Test pack help output — shows all options\n169: \n170: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_pack_command.py -v` — all pass\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## T14. CLI — Add `publish` Command Tests\n175: \n176: The `publish` CLI command has no dedicated test file.\n177: \n178: - [ ] 14.1 Test successful publish with `--provider agentcube` — exit code 0, shows Agent ID and Endpoint\n179: - [ ] 14.2 Test successful publish with `--provider k8s` — exit code 0, shows Deployment, Service, URL\n180: - [ ] 14.3 Test unsupported provider — exit code 1, error message\n181: - [ ] 14.4 Test invalid node port (below 30000) — exit code 1, error message\n182: - [ ] 14.5 Test invalid node port (above 32767) — exit code 1, error message\n183: - [ ] 14.6 Test publish with `--namespace`, `--replicas`, `--node-port` options\n184: - [ ] 14.7 Test publish help output — shows all options\n185: \n186: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_publish_command.py -v` — all pass\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## T15. CLI — Add `invoke` Command Provider Routing Tests\n191: \n192: Verify the `--provider` flag correctly routes in the CLI invoke command.\n193: \n194: - [ ] 15.1 Test `--provider agentcube` invokes `InvokeRuntime` with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n195: - [ ] 15.2 Test `--provider k8s` invokes `InvokeRuntime` with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n196: - [ ] 15.3 Test default provider is `agentcube` when `--provider` is omitted\n197: \n198: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_invoke_command.py -v -k provider` — all pass\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ## T16. CLI — Add `status` Command Provider Routing Tests\n203: \n204: Verify the `--provider` flag correctly routes in the CLI status command.\n205: \n206: - [ ] 16.1 Test `--provider agentcube` queries AgentRuntime CR status\n207: - [ ] 16.2 Test `--provider k8s` queries Deployment status\n208: - [ ] 16.3 Test default provider is `agentcube` when `--provider` is omitted\n209: \n210: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_status_command.py -v -k provider` — all pass\n211: \n212: ---\n213: \n214: ## T17. Integration — Publish E2E (Mocked)\n215: \n216: End-to-end test for the publish flow with mocked K8s/Docker.\n217: \n218: - [ ] 17.1 Test full publish flow: pack → build (mocked) → publish (mocked K8s) → verify metadata updated\n219: - [ ] 17.2 Test publish with `--provider k8s` end-to-end: verifies Deployment + Service creation, wait for ready, metadata update\n220: - [ ] 17.3 Test publish with `--provider agentcube` end-to-end: verifies AgentRuntime CR creation, metadata update\n221: \n222: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_publish_e2e.py -v` — all pass\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ## T18. Integration — Invoke E2E (Mocked)\n227: \n228: End-to-end test for the invoke flow with mocked HTTP.\n229: \n230: - [ ] 18.1 Test full invoke flow: publish (mocked) → invoke (mocked HTTP) → verify response\n231: - [ ] 18.2 Test invoke with custom headers end-to-end\n232: - [ ] 18.3 Test invoke with session ID end-to-end — verifies `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header\n233: \n234: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_invoke_e2e.py -v` — all pass\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## T19. Integration — Status E2E (Mocked)\n239: \n240: End-to-end test for the status flow with mocked K8s.\n241: \n242: - [ ] 19.1 Test full status flow: publish (mocked) → status (mocked K8s) → verify Rich table output\n243: - [ ] 19.2 Test status for unpublished agent — exit code 1, guidance message\n244: - [ ] 19.3 Test status for deleted agent — shows `not_found` or `not_found_in_k8s`\n245: \n246: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_status_e2e.py -v` — all pass\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ## T20. Test/Code Ratio Verification\n251: \n252: Ensure test-to-code ratio meets TDD manifest requirement (> 0.4).\n253: \n254: - [ ] 20.1 Count source lines in `cmd/cli/agentcube/` (exclude `__pycache__`, `__init__.py`)\n255: - [ ] 20.2 Count test lines in `cmd/cli/tests/` (exclude `__pycache__`, `__init__.py`)\n256: - [ ] 20.3 Verify ratio > 0.4; if not, add missing tests\n257: - [ ] 20.4 Verify every source file has a corresponding test file (per TDD manifest)\n258: \n259: **Verification:** Run `find cmd/cli/agentcube -name '*.py' ! -name '__init__.py' | xargs wc -l` and `find cmd/cli/tests -name '*.py' ! -name '__init__.py' | xargs wc -l`, compute ratio\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ## T21. Full Test Suite Green\n264: \n265: Run the complete test suite to ensure no regressions.\n266: \n267: - [ ] 21.1 `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v` — all tests pass\n268: - [ ] 21.2 `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` — coverage report generated\n269: - [ ] 21.3 No import errors or type errors in test files\n270: \n271: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v --tb=short` — 0 failures, 0 errors\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ## Task Dependencies\n276: \n277: ```\n278: T1 ──→ T2 ──→ T3\n279: T4 ──→ T5\n280: T6 (parallel with T1-T5)\n281: T7 ──→ T10\n282: T8 (parallel)\n283: T9 (parallel)\n284: T11 (parallel)\n285: T12 (parallel)\n286: T13 ──┐\n287: T14 ──┼──→ T17 ──→ T21\n288: T15 ──┤\n289: T16 ──┘\n290: T18 ──→ T21\n291: T19 ──→ T21\n292: T20 ──→ T21\n293: ```\n294: \n295: ## Parallelizable Groups\n296: \n297: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n298: |-------|-------|---------------|\n299: | G1 — Provider Core | T1, T4, T6 | None |\n300: | G2 — Provider Extensions | T2, T3, T5 | T1, T4 |\n301: | G3 — Runtime Logic | T7, T8, T9, T10, T11, T12 | None |\n302: | G4 — CLI Commands | T13, T14, T15, T16 | None |\n303: | G5 — Integration | T17, T18, T19 | T14, T15, T16 |\n304: | G6 — Verification | T20, T21 | All above |\n305: \n306: ---\n307: \n308: ## Acceptance Criteria\n309: \n310: | # | Criterion | Command |\n311: |---|-----------|---------|\n312: | AC1 | All provider tests pass (K8s + AgentCube) | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/ -v` |\n313: | AC2 | All runtime tests pass (publish, status, invoke) | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/ -v` |\n314: | AC3 | All CLI command tests pass (pack, build, publish, invoke, status) | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/ -v` |\n315: | AC4 | All integration tests pass | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/integration/ -v` |\n316: | AC5 | Test/code ratio > 0.4 | `cat /dev/null` (manual verification in T20) |\n317: | AC6 | Every source file has a corresponding test file | `cat /dev/null` (manual verification in T20) |\n318: | AC7 | Full test suite green with 0 failures | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v --tb=short` |\n319: | AC8 | `kubectl-agentcube --version` prints version | `python -m agentcube.cli.main --version` |\n320: | AC9 | `kubectl-agentcube --help` shows all 5 commands | `python -m agentcube.cli.main --help` |\n321: | AC10 | Provider flag `--provider agentcube` and `--provider k8s` work for publish/invoke/status | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/ -v -k provider` |\n\n(End of file - total 321 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd/cli\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-026/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-026/design.md`, `changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** None\n\n## T1. KubernetesProvider — Fill Test Gaps\n\nStrengthen `KubernetesProvider` test coverage for auto-assigned NodePort, entrypoint parsing, and env var propagation.\n\n- [ ] 1.1 Test auto-assigned NodePort (no node_port arg) — verify `deploy_agent` returns the auto-assigned port from the created Service\n- [ ] 1.2 Test entrypoint parsing — verify `\"python main.py arg1\"` splits into `command=[\"python\"]`, `args=[\"main.py\", \"arg1\"]`\n- [ ] 1.3 Test empty entrypoint — verify `entrypoint=\"\"` produces `command=None`, `args=None`\n- [ ] 1.4 Test env_vars propagation — verify `V1EnvVar` objects are created with correct key/value pairs\n- [ ] 1.5 Test deployment labels — verify `labels={\"app\": sanitized_name}` are set on the pod template\n- [ ] 1.6 Test namespace in return dict — verify `namespace` key is present in the result dict\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775862281637,"end":1775862281652}}}}
